Red Pepper, Potato, and Peanut Sabzi
  --Priya Krishna & Ritu Krishna

2 tbsp evoo
1 tsp cumin seeds
1 tsp fennel seeds
1 small yellow onion, cut into 1/2" pieces
1 large russet potato, cut into 1/2" pieces
2 medium red bell peppers, cut into 3/4" pieces
1 tsp kosher salt
1/4 c roasted, unsalted peanuts, crushed
1 tbsp (ore more) fresh lime juice (~1/2 lime)

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium high heat until shimmering. Add cumin seeds and cook, stirring, until they turn a medium shade of brown, ~1 min. Reduce heat to medium and stir in fennel seeds. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent, 4-6 min. Stir in potato, then spread mixture into an even layer in pan. Cover and cook until potato is tender and not mushy, a little charring on the bottom is ok, 7-10 min. Stir in bell pepper and salt. Cover and cook until peppers are slightly softened, 5-7 min. Scrape up fond from bottom of pan and stir into mixture. Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts and lime juice, tasting to adjust seasoning as needed.


Notes: potatoes may take longer to cook
